===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Some scholars identify an oracle bone character {{Han compound|ж—Ҙ|й Ғ|ls=ic|t1=sun|t2=head; man|nocap=1}} as this character вҖ“ a man under the scorching sun; summer. However, it only appears as a diviner's name, making the identification uncertain.

In {{w|Spring and Autumn period}} bronze inscriptions, various variants appeared. {{zh-l|*жӯў|foot}} was often added below the man, and in some forms {{zh-l|*ж—Ҙ}} was removed while {{zh-l|*рҰҘ‘|two hands}} was added. The seal script inherits from the latter form, with {{zh-l|*жӯў}} replaced by the related {{zh-l|*еӨҠ}}.

{{w|Warring States period}} forms also varied. The bamboo and silk script above shows a common form: {{Han compound|ж—Ҙ|жӯў|й Ғ}}. The "ancient script" ({{zh-l|*еҸӨж–Ү}}) in ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' (labelled as large seal script) has deviated significantly, with {{zh-l|*жӯў}} becoming {{zh-l|*и¶і}} and the top part possibly a corruption of {{zh-l|*й Ғ}}.

The current form derives from the seal script, with {{zh-l|*рҰҘ‘}} and the legs of {{zh-l|*й Ғ}} removed. Unrelated to [[еӨҚ]].

===Etymology 1===
; вҖңgreat; Xia Dynasty; China; ChineseвҖқ
: Possibly related to {{och-l|еҒҮ|great}}, {{och-l|еҳҸ|great}} and {{och-l|е»Ҳ|big house}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1980}}). {{zh-ref|Shi (2000)}} and {{zh-ref|Mair (2013)}} relate this word to {{cog|bo|аҪўаҫ’аҫұ||great; wide; width; size; expanse; China}}.

; вҖңmagnificent colours; variegatedвҖқ
: The sense вҖңvariegatedвҖқ may be of a different origin. Compare {{cog|sit-pro||*KrДҒ(H)|variegated}} ({{zh-ref|Starostin}}), whence {{cog|bo|аҪ–аҪҖаҫІ||variegated; bright; radiant; splendid}}, {{cog|bo|аҪҒаҫІ||many-coloured; variegated; mottled; striped}} and {{cog|my|бҖҖбҖ»бҖ¬бҖё||variegated; striped; chequered}}. Possibly related to {{och-l|йЁў|horse with mixed red and white colour}}.

